## The Future: Where MTA is Headed

### Trend 1: Unified Measurement

Pure MTA is being replaced by triangulated approaches combining MTA + MMM + model flexibility. Platforms like Lifesight, Funnel, and SegmentStream are leading this shift.

### Trend 2: Privacy-First / Cookieless

With iOS ATT and Chrome deprecating third-party cookies (eventually), AI-driven and first-party data approaches are the way forward. SegmentStream's visit scoring and Lifesight's causal AI represent this future.

### Trend 3: Consolidation

Expect acquisitions: Adobe bought Bizible, AppLovin bought Adjust. Smaller players will be acquired or fade as the market matures.

### Trend 4: AI Everywhere

Every tool now claims "AI-powered" attribution. The meaningful distinction is whether AI is cosmetic (chatbots on top of reports) or substantive (ML models that actually improve measurement accuracy).

